Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @aubergine{2%unit}(each halved lengthways). Score a diamond pattern into
the flesh of each half, taking care not to cut too deeply.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1%unit}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Trim the @cucumber{1%unit}(trimmed, halved lengthways) and chop into 1cm wide,
5cm long batons.

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp} and a drizzle of
@oil{to taste}.

Add garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @jasmine rice{150%grams}, @salt{1%tsp} and @water{300%ml} (double both
for 4p). Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the #lid{} and cook for
~{12%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or
until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @sesame seeds{1%sachet}, stirring regularly, until
lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Once toasted remove from the pan and set
aside.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Place the aubergine halves, skin-side down, into the pan.

Fry until the aubergine is golden brown, ~{4%minutes} on each side.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{} mix the @red wine vinegar{2%sachet} with
@water{2%tbsp} and @sugar{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Add the cucumber and sliced onion and set aside.

Gently toss the veg at regular intervals to coat in the vinegar.

In a small bowl mix the @miso paste{1%sachet}, @soy sauce{1%sachet},
@sesame oil{20%ml} and @sugar{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Pour into the pan and cook with aubergine now cut-side down for
~{1-2%minutes}.

Place the aubergine halves, skin-side down, into an #oven dish{}.

Pour any remaining marinade over the aubergine and sprinkle over half the
sesame seeds.

Bake the aubergine in the #oven{} until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Stir the remaining sesame seeds through the rice, fluffing it up as you go.

Divide the fragrant rice between #bowls{}.

Serve the roasted aubergine and (drained) pickled veg alongside.